Explanation:
The problem requires reversing the bits of a 32-bit unsigned integer. We can achieve this by iterating from 0 to 31 (since there are 32 bits in a 32-bit integer) and performing bitwise operations. The algorithm uses a temporary variable `result` to store the reversed bits and shifts it left (<<) to combine the bits and ORs it with the least significant bit (`n & 1`) to include it. Then, we shift the input `n` right (>>) to clear the least significant bit before moving on to the next bit. This process is repeated for all 32 bits, resulting in an efficient solution with a time complexity of O(1) and space complexity of O(1).

